obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (41410)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41410&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) This Act may be called the Employees' Provident`
  line `Funds and Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1952.]`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2***.`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Subject to the provisions contained in section 16, it applies--`
  line
  line `(a) to every establishment which is a factory engaged in any industry specified in Schedule I and`
  line `in which ^4[twenty] or more persons are employed, and`
  line
  line `(b) to any other establishment employing ^4[twenty] or more persons or class of such`
  line `establishments which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in`
  line `this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, after giving not less than two months notice of its`
  line `intention so to do, by notification in the Official Gazette, apply the provisions of this Act to any`
  line `establishment employing such number of persons less than ^4[twenty] as may be specified in the`
  line notification.
  line
  line `^5[(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3) of this section or sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 16, where it appears to the Central Provident Fund Commissioner, whether on an application`
  line `made to him in this behalf or otherwise, that the employer and the majority of employees in relation to`
  line `any establishment have agreed that the provisions of this Act should be made applicable to the`
  line `establishment, he may, by notification in the Official Gazette, apply the provisions of this Act to that`
  line `establishment on and from the date of such agreement or from any subsequent date specified in such`
  line agreement.]
  line
  line `^6[(5) An establishment to which this Act applies shall continue to be governed by this Act`
  line `notwithstanding that the number of persons employed therein at any time falls below twenty.]`
  line
  line `^7* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 99 of 1976, s. 17, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line
  line `2. The Words except the State of Jammu and Kashmir omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-`
  line `2019) and extended to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Union territory of Ladakh by notification No. S.O.`
  line `3962(E), Part II-section 3-Sub-section (ii) dated 31-10-20 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 94 of 1956, s. 2, for sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 46 of 1960, s. 2, for "fifty" (w.e.f. 31-12-1960).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 33 of 1988, s. 2, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 46 of 1960, s. 2 (w.e.f. 31-12-1960).`
  line
  line `7. The proviso omitted by Act 16 of 1971, s. 13 (w.e.f. 23-4-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (41411)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41411&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line
  line `^1[(a) "appropriate Government" means--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to an establishment belonging to, or under the control of, the Central`
  line `Government or in relation to an establishment connected with a railway company, a major port, a`
  line `mine or an oilfield or a controlled industry, ^2[or in relation to an establishment having`
  line `departments or branches in more than one State], the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to any other establishment, the State Government;]`
  line
  line `^3[(aa) "authorised officer" means the Central Provident Fund Commissioner, Additional Central`
  line `Provident Fund Commissioner, Deputy Provident Fund Commissioner, Regional Provident Fund`
  line `Commissioner or such other officer as may be authorised by the Central Government, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette;]`
  line
  line `(b) "basic wages" means all emoluments which are earned by an employee while on duty or ^4[on`
  line `leave or on holidays with wages in either case] in accordance with the terms of the contract of`
  line `employment and which are paid or payable in cash to him, but does not include`
  line
  line `(i) the cash value of any food concession;`
  line
  line `(ii) any dearness allowance (that is to say, all cash payments by whatever name called paid to`
  line `an employee on account of a rise in the cost of living), house-rent allowance, overtime allowance,`
  line `bonus commission or any other similar allowance payable to the employee in respect of his`
  line `employment or of work done in such employment;`
  line
  line `(iii) any presents made by the employer;`
  line
  line `(c) "contribution" means a contribution payable in respect of a member under a Scheme`
  line `^5[or the`
  line `contribution payable in respect of an employee to whom the Insurance Scheme applies];`
  line
  line `(d) "controlled industry" means any industry the control of which by the Union has been declared`
  line `by a Central Act to be expedient in the public interest;`
  line
  line `^6[(e) "employer" means--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to an establishment which is a factory, the owner or occupier of the factory,`
  line `including the agent of such owner or occupier, the legal representative of a deceased owner or`
  line `occupier and, where a person has been named as a manager of the factory under clause (f) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 7 of the Factories Act, 1948 (63 of 1948), the person so named; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to any other establishment, the person who, or the authority which, has the`
  line `ultimate control over the affairs of the establishment, and where the said affairs are entrusted to a`
  line `manager, managing director or managing agent, such manager, managing director or managing`
  line agent;]
  line
  line `(f) "employee" means any person who is employed for wages in any kind of work, manual or`
  line `otherwise, in or in connection with the work of ^7[an establishment], and who gets his wages directly`
  line `or indirectly from the employer, ^8[and includes any person--`
  line
  line `(i) employed by or through a contractor in or in connection with the work of the`
  line establishment;
  line
  line `(ii) engaged as an apprentice, not being an apprentice engaged under the Apprentices Act,`
  line `1961 (52 of 1961), or under the standing orders of the establishment;]`
  line
  line `^9[(ff) "exempted employee" means an employee to whom a Scheme ^10[or the Insurance Scheme, as`
  line `the case may be], would, but for the exemption granted under ^11*** section 17, have applied;`
  line
  line `(fff) "exempted ^12[establishment]" means ^13[an establishment] in respect of which an exemption has`
  line `has been granted under section 17 from the operation of all or any of the provisions of any Scheme`
  line `^10[or the Insurance Scheme, as the case may be], whether such exemption has been granted to the`
  line `^12[establishment] as such or to any person or class of persons employed therein;]`
  line
  line `(g) "factory" means any premises, including the precincts thereof, in any part of which a`
  line `manufacturing process is being carried on or is ordinarily so carried on, whether with the aid of power`
  line `or without the aid of power;`
  line
  line `^14* * * * *`
  line
  line `(h) "Fund" means the provident fund established under a Scheme;`
  line
  line `(i) "industry" means any industry specified in Schedule I, and includes any other industry added`
  line `to the Schedule by notification under section 4;`
  line
  line `^10[(ia) "Insurance Fund" means the Deposit-linked Insurance Fund established under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 6C;`
  line
  line `(ib) "Insurance Scheme" means the Employees Deposit-linked Insurance Scheme framed under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 6C;]`
  line
  line ^15[
  line `^16[(ic)] "manufacture" or "manufacturing process" means any process for making, altering,`
  line `repairing, ornamenting, finishing, packing, oiling, washing, cleaning, breaking up, demolishing or`
  line `otherwise treating or adapting any article or substance with a view to its use, sale, transport, delivery`
  line `or disposal;]`
  line
  line `(j) "member" means a member of the Fund;`
  line
  line `(k) "occupier of a factory" means the person who has ultimate control over the affairs of the`
  line `factory, and, where the said affairs are entrusted to a managing agent, such agent shall be deemed to`
  line `be the occupier of the factory;`
  line
  line `^17[(kA) "Pension Fund" means the Employees' Pension Fund established under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 6A;`
  line
  line `(kB) "Pension Scheme" means the Employees' Pension Scheme framed under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 6A;]`
  line
  line `^18[(ka) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(kb) "Recovery Officer" means any officer of the Central Government, State Government or the`
  line `Board of Trustees constituted under section 5A, who may be authorised by the Central Government,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, to exercise the powers of a Recovery Officer under this Act;]`
  line
  line `^19[(l) "Scheme" means the Employees' Provident Fund Scheme framed under section 5;]`
  line
  line `^20[(ll) "Superannuation", in relation to an employee, who is the member of the Pension Scheme`
  line `means the attainment, by the said employee, of the age of fifty-eight years;]`
  line
  line `^21[(m) “Tribunal” means the Industrial Tribunal referred to in section 7 D].`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 1958, s. 2, for clause (a).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 22 of 1965, s. 2 (w.e.f. 24-11-1964).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 33 of 1988, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "on leave with wages" (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 99 of 1976, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 94 of 1956, s. 4, for clause (e).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by ibid., s. 3, for "a factory".`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 33 of 1988, s. 3, for "and includes any person employed by or through a contractor in or in connection with the`
  line `work of the establishment" (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 37 of 1953, s. 3.`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 99 of 1976, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line
  line `11. The words, brackets and figure "sub-section (1) of" omitted by Act 28 of 1963, s. 2 (w.e.f. 30-11-1963).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by Act 94 of 1956, s. 3, for "factory".`
  line
  line `13. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "a factory".`
  line
  line `14. Omitted by Act 25 of 1996, s. 3 (w.e.f. 16-11-1995).`
  line
  line `15. Subs. by Act 28 of 1963, s. 2, for clause (ia) (w.e.f. 30-11-1963).`
  line
  line `16. Clause (ia) re-lettered as clause (ic) by Act 99 of 1976, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line
  line `17. Ins. by Act 25 of 1996, s. 3 (w.e.f. 16-11-1995).`
  line
  line `18. Ins. by Act 33 of 1988, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line
  line `19. Subs. by Act 16 of 1971, s. 14, for clause (l) (w.e.f. 23-4-1971).`
  line
  line `20. Ins. by Act 25 of 1996, s. 3 (w.e.f. 16-11-1995).`
  line
  line `21. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 159 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a:
  sectionId (41412)
  sectionNo 2A
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment to include all departments and branches.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 46 of 1960, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31-12-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41412&sectionno=2A&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[2A. Establishment to include all departments and branches.--For the removal of doubts, it is`
  line `hereby declared that where an establishment consists of different departments or has branches, whether`
  line `situate in the same place or in different places, all such departments or branches shall be treated as parts`
  line `of the same establishment.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (41851)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 4
  title `Power to apply Act to an establishment which has a common provident fund with another establishment`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 94 of 1956, s. 5, for section 3.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41851&sectionno=3&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[3. Power to apply Act to an establishment which has a common provident fund with another`
  line `establishment.--Where immediately before this Act becomes applicable to an establishment there is in`
  line `existence a provident fund which is common to the employees employed in that establishment and`
  line `employees in any other establishment, the Central Government may, by notification in Official Gazette,`
  line `direct that the provisions of this Act shall also apply to such other establishment.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (41414)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power to add to Schedule I.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41414&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, add to Schedule I any other industry in respect of the employees whereof it is of opinion that a`
  line `provident fund scheme should be framed under this Act, and thereupon the industry so added shall be`
  line `deemed to be an industry specified in Schedule I for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) All notifications under sub-section (1) shall be laid before Parliament, as soon as may be, after`
  line `they are issued.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (41415)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Employees‟ Provident Fund Schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41415&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] The Central Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, frame a Scheme to be called the Employees' Provident Fund Scheme for the`
  line `establishment of provident funds under this Act for employees or for any class of employees and specify`
  line `the ^2[establishments] or class of ^2[establishments] to which the said Scheme shall apply ^3[and there shall`
  line `be established, as soon as may be after the framing of the Scheme, a Fund in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act and the Scheme].`
  line
  line `^4[(1A) The Fund shall vest in, and be administered by, the Central Board constituted under section`
  line 5A.
  line
  line `(1B) Subject to the provisions of this Act, a Scheme framed under sub-section (1) may provide for all`
  line `or any of the matters specified in Schedule II.]`
  line
  line `^5[(2) A Scheme framed under sub-section (1) may provide that any of its provisions shall take effect`
  line `either prospectively or retrospectively on such date as may be specified in this behalf in the Scheme.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 5 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 37 of 1953, s. 4.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 94 of 1956, s. 3, for "factories".`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 37 of 1953, s. 4.`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 28 of 1963, s. 3 (w.e.f. 30-11-1963).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 37 of 1953, s. 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (41416)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 7
  title `Central Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41416&sectionno=5A&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A. Central Board.--(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `constitute, with effect from such date as may be specified therein, a Board of Trustees for the territories to`
  line `which this Act extends (hereinafter in this Act referred to as the Central Board) consisting of the`
  line `following ^2[persons as members] namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) ^3[a Chairman and a Vice-Chairman] to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `^4[(aa) the Central Provident Fund Commissioner, ex officio;]`
  line
  line `(b) not more than five persons appointed by the Central Government from amongst its officials;`
  line
  line `(c) not more than fifteen persons representing Governments of such States as the Central`
  line `Government may specify in this behalf, appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) ^5[ten persons] representing employers of the establishments to which the Scheme applies,`
  line `appointed by the Central Government after consultation with such organisations of employers as may`
  line `be recognised by the Central Government in this behalf; and`
  line
  line `(e) ^5[ten persons] representing employees in the establishments to which the Scheme applies,`
  line `appointed by the Central Government after consultation with such organisations of employees as may`
  line `be recognised by the Central Government in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions subject to which a member of the Central Board may be appointed and`
  line `the time, place and procedure of the meetings of the Central Board shall be such as may be provided for`
  line `in the Scheme.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Board shall ^6[, subject to the provisions of section 6A ^7[and section 6C,]] administer`
  line `the Fund vested in it in such manner as may be specified in the Scheme.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Board shall perform such other functions as it may be required to perform by or under`
  line `any provisions of the Scheme ^8[, the ^9[Pension] Scheme and the Insurance Scheme].`
  line
  line `^10[(5) The Central Board shall maintain proper accounts of its income and expenditure in such form`
  line `and in such manner as the Central Government may, after consultation with the Comptroller and AuditorGeneral of India, specify in the Scheme.`
  line
  line `(6) The accounts of the Central Board shall be audited annually by the Comptroller and AuditorGeneral of India and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such audit shall be payable by`
  line `the Central Board to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(7) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Central Board shall have the same rights and privileges and authority`
  line `in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General has, in connection with the audit of`
  line `Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of books, accounts,`
  line `connected vouchers, documents and papers and inspect any of the offices of the Central Board.`
  line
  line `(8) The accounts of the Central Board as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or`
  line `any other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded to the Central Board which shall forward the same to the Central Government along with its comments on`
  line `the report of the Comptroller and Auditor-General.`
  line
  line `(9) It shall be the duty of the Central Board to submit also to the Central Government an annual report`
  line `of its work and activities and the Central Government shall cause a copy of the annual report, the audited`
  line `accounts together with the report of the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and the comments of`
  line `the Central Board thereon to be laid before each House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 1963, s. 4 (w.e.f. 30-11-1963).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 1988, s. 4, for "persons" (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "a chairman" (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "six persons" (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 16 of 1971, s. 15 (w.e.f. 23-4-1971).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 99 of 1976, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for "and the Family Pension Scheme" (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 25 of 1996, s. 4, for "Family Pension" (w.e.f. 16-11-1995).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 33 of 1988, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-8-1988)`
obj_root_law_sections_5_aa:
  sectionId (41417)
  sectionNo 5AA
  orderNo 8
  title `Executive Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_aa_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 1988, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41417&sectionno=5AA&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_5_aa_content:
  string
  line `^1[5AA. Executive Committee.-- (1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, constitute, with effect from such date as may be specified therein, an Executive Committee to`
  line `assist the Central Board in the performance of its functions.`
  line
  line `(2) The Executive Committee shall consist of the following persons as members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman appointed by the Central Government from amongst the members of the Central`
  line Board;
  line
  line `(b) two persons appointed by the Central Government from amongst the persons referred to in`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 5A;`
  line
  line `(c) three persons appointed by the Central Government from amongst the persons referred to in`
  line `clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 5A;`
  line
  line `(d) three persons representing the employers elected by the Central Board from amongst the`
  line `persons referred to in clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 5A;`
  line
  line `(e) three persons representing the employees elected by the Central Board from amongst the`
  line `persons referred to in clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 5A;`
  line
  line `(f) the Central Provident Fund Commissioner, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(3) The terms and conditions subject to which a member of the Central Board may be appointed or`
  line `elected to the Executive Committee and the time, place and procedure of the meetings of the Executive`
  line `Committee shall be such as may be provided for in the Scheme.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_b:
  sectionId (41418)
  sectionNo 5B
  orderNo 9
  title `State Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 1963, s. 4.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41418&sectionno=5B&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_5_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[5B. State Board.-- (1) The Central Government may, after consultation with the Government of any`
  line `State, by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute for that State a Board of Trustees (hereinafter in`
  line `this Act referred to as the State Board) in such manner as may be provided for in the Scheme.`
  line
  line `(2) A State Board shall exercise such powers and perform such duties as the Central Government may`
  line `assign to it from time to time.`
  line
  line `(3) The terms and conditions subject to which a member of a State Board may be appointed and the`
  line `time, place and procedure of the meetings of a State Board shall be such as may be provided for in the`
  line Scheme.]
obj_root_law_sections_5_c:
  sectionId (41419)
  sectionNo 5C
  orderNo 10
  title `Board of Trustees to be body corporate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 1963, s. 4.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41419&sectionno=5C&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_5_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[5C. Board of Trustees to body corporate.-- Every Board of Trustees constituted under section`
  line `5A or section 5B shall be a body corporate under the name specified in the notification constituting it,`
  line `having perpetual succession and a common seal and shall by the said name sue and be sued.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_d:
  sectionId (41420)
  sectionNo 5D
  orderNo 11
  title `Appointment of officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41420&sectionno=5D&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_5_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[5D. Appointment of officers.-- (1) The Central Government shall appoint a Central Provident Fund`
  line `Commissioner who shall be the chief executive officer of the Central Board and shall be subject to the`
  line `general control and superintendence of that Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may also appoint ^2[a Financial Adviser and Chief Accounts Officers] to`
  line `assist the Central Provident Fund Commissioner in the discharge of his duties.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Board may appoint ^3[, subject to the maximum scale of pay, as may be specified in`
  line `the Scheme, as many Additional Central Provident Fund Commissioners, Deputy Provident Fund`
  line `Commissioners, Regional Provident Fund Commissioners, Assistant Provident Fund Commissioners and]`
  line `such other officers and employees as it may consider necessary for the efficient administration of the`
  line `Scheme ^4[, the ^5[Pension Scheme and the Insurance Scheme].`
  line
  line `(4) No appointment to ^6[the post of the Central Provident Fund Commissioner or an Additional`
  line `Central Provident Fund Commissioner or a Financial Adviser and Chief Accounts Officer or any other`
  line `post under the Central Board carrying a scale of pay equivalent to the scale of pay of any Group 'A' or`
  line `Group 'B' post under the Central Government] shall be made except after consultation with the Union`
  line `Public Service Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such consultation shall be necessary in regard to any such appointment--`
  line
  line `(a) for a period not exceeding one year; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the person to be appointed is at the time of his appointment--`
  line
  line `(i) a member of the Indian Administrative Service, or`
  line
  line `(ii) in the service of the Central Government or a State Government or the Central Board in a`
  line `^7[Group 'A' or Group 'B' post].`
  line
  line `(5) A State Board may, with the approval of the State Government concerned, appoint such staff as it`
  line `may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(6) The method of recruitment, salary and allowances, discipline and other conditions of service of`
  line `the Central Provident Fund Commissioner, ^8[and the Financial Adviser and Chief Accounts Officer] shall`
  line `be such as may be specified by the Central Government and such salary and allowances shall be paid out`
  line `of the Fund.`
  line
  line `^9[(7) (a) The method of recruitment, salary and allowances, discipline and other conditions of service`
  line `of the Additional Central Provident Fund Commissioner, Deputy Provident Fund Commissioner,`
  line `Regional Provident Fund Commissioner, Assistant Provident Fund Commissioner and other officers and`
  line `employees of the Central Board shall be such as may be specified by the Central Board in accordance`
  line `with the rules and orders applicable to the officers and employees of the Central Government drawing`
  line `corresponding scales of pay:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Central Board is of the opinion that it is necessary to make a departure from`
  line `the said rules or orders in respect of any of the matters aforesaid, it shall obtain the prior approval of the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(b) In determining the corresponding scales of pay of officers and employees under clause (a), the`
  line `Central Board shall have regard to the educational qualifications, method of recruitment, duties and`
  line `responsibilities of such officers and employees under the Central Government and in case of any doubt,`
  line `the Central Board shall refer the matter to the Central Government whose decision thereon shall be final.]`
  line
  line `(8) The method of recruitment, salary and allowances, discipline and other conditions of service of`
  line `officers and employees of a State Board shall be such as may be specified by that Board, with the`
  line `approval of the State Government concerned.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_d_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 1963, s. 4.`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 1988, s. 6, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by, s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 99 of 1976, s. 20, for "and the Family Pension Scheme" (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 1996, s. 4, for "Family Pension" (w.e.f. 16-11-1995).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 33 of 1988, s. 6, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "Class I or Class II post" (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "Deputy Provident Fund Commissioner and Regional Provident Fund Commissioner"`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line `9. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for sub-section (7) (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_dd:
  sectionId (41852)
  sectionNo 5DD
  orderNo 12
  title `Acts and proceedings of the Central Board or its Executive Committee or the State Board not to be invalidated on certain grounds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_dd_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 1988, s. 7. (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41852&sectionno=5DD&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_5_dd_content:
  string
  line `^1[5DD. Acts and proceedings of the Central Board or its Executive Committee or the State`
  line `Board not to be in validated on certain grounds.-- No act done or proceeding taken by the Central`
  line `Board or the Executive Committee constituted under section 5AA or the State Board shall be questioned`
  line `on the ground merely of the existence of any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Central`
  line `Board or the Executive Committee or the State Board, as the case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_e:
  sectionId (41422)
  sectionNo 5E
  orderNo 13
  title Delegation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41422&sectionno=5E&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_5_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[5E. Delegation.-- ^2[The Central Board may delegate to the Executive Committee or to the Chairman`
  line `of the Board or to any of its officers and a State Board may delegate to its Chairman or to any of its`
  line `officers] subject to such conditions and limitations, if any, as it may specify, such of its powers and`
  line `functions under this Act as it may deem necessary for the efficient administration of the Scheme ^3[, the`
  line `^4[Pension] Scheme and the Insurance Scheme].]]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_e_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 1963, s. 4.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 99 of 1976, s. 20, for "and the Family Pension Scheme" (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 25 of 1996, s. 4, for "Family Pension" (w.e.f. 16-11-1995).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (41423)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 14
  title `Contributions and matters which may be provided for in Schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41423&sectionno=6&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1*** The contribution`
  line `which shall be paid by the employer to the Fund shall be ^2[ten per cent.] of the basic wages, ^3[dearness`
  line `allowance and retaining allowance (if any)] for the time being payable to each of the employees`
  line `^4[(whether employed by him directly or by or through a contractor)], and the employees' contribution`
  line `shall be equal to the contribution payable by the employer in respect of him and may, ^5[if any employee`
  line `so desires, be an amount exceeding ^2[ten per cent.] of his basic wages, dearness allowance and retaining`
  line `allowance (if any), subject to the condition that the employer shall not be under an obligation to pay any`
  line `contribution over and above his contribution payable under this section]:`
  line
  line `^6[Provided that in its application to any establishment or class of establishments which the Central`
  line `Government, after making such inquiry as it deems fit, may, by notification in the Official Gazette`
  line `specify, this section shall be subject to the modification that for the words ^2[ten per cent.], at both the`
  line `places where they occur, the words^7[twelve per cent.] shall be substituted:]`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the amount of any contribution payable under this Act involves a fraction`
  line `of a rupee, the Scheme may provide for the rounding off of such fraction to the nearest rupee, half of a`
  line `rupee or quarter of a rupee.`
  line
  line `^8[Explanation 1.] -- For the purposes of this 13[section], dearness allowance shall be deemed to`
  line `include also the cash value of any food concession allowed to the employee.`
  line
  line `^10[Explanation 2].-- For the purposes of this ^9[section], "retaining allowance" means an allowance`
  line `payable for the time being to an employee of any factory or other establishment during any period in`
  line `which the establishment is not working, for retaining his services.]`
  line
  line `^11* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The brackets and figure "(1)" omitted by Act 28 of 1963, s. 5 (w.e.f. 30-11-1963).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 10 of 1998, s. 2, for "eight and one-third per cent." (w.e.f. 22-9-1997).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 46 of 1960, s. 4, for "and the dearness allowance" (w.e.f. 31-12-1960).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 28 of 1963, s. 5 (w.e.f. 30-11-1963).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 33 of 1988, s. 9, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for the First Proviso (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 10 of 1998, s. 2, for "ten per cent." (w.e.f. 22-9-1997).`
  line
  line `8. The Explanation. re-numbered as Explanation 1 by Act 46 of 1960, s. 4 (w.e.f. 31-12-1960).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 28 of 1963, s. 5, for "sub-section" (w.e.f. 30-11-1963).`
  line
  line `10. The Explanation ins. by Act 46 of 1960, s. 4 (w.e.f. 31-12-1960).`
  line
  line `11. Omitted by Act 28 of 1963, s. 5 (w.e.f. 30-11-1963).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (41424)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 15
  title `Employees' Pension Scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 25 of 1996, s. 5, for sections 6A and 6B (w.e.f. 16-11-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41424&sectionno=6A&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[6A. Employees' Pension Scheme.-- (1) The Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, frame a scheme to be called the Employees' Pension Scheme for the purpose of`
  line `providing for--`
  line
  line `(a) superannuation pension, retiring pension or permanent total disablement pension to the`
  line `employees of any establishment or class of establishments to which this Act applies; and`
  line
  line `(b) widow or widowers pension, children pension or orphan pension payable to the beneficiaries`
  line `of such employees.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 6, there shall be established, as soon as may be`
  line `after framing of the Pension Scheme, a Pension Fund into which there shall be paid, from time to time, in`
  line `respect of every employee who is a member of the Pension Scheme,--`
  line
  line `(a) such sums from the employer's contribution under section 6, not exceeding eight and`
  line `one-third per cent. of the basic wages, dearness allowance and retaining allowance, if any, of the`
  line `concerned employees, as may be specified in the Pension Scheme;`
  line
  line `(b) such sums as are payable by the employers of exempted establishments under sub-section (6)`
  line `of section 17;`
  line
  line `(c) the net assets of the Employees' Family Pension Fund as on the date of the establishment of`
  line `the Pension Fund;`
  line
  line `(d) such sums as the Central Government may, after due appropriation by Parliament by law in`
  line `this behalf, specify.`
  line
  line `(3) On the establishment of the Pension Fund, the Family Pension Scheme (hereinafter referred to as`
  line `the ceased scheme) shall cease to operate and all assets of the ceased scheme shall vest in and shall stand`
  line `transferred to, and all liabilities under the ceased scheme shall be enforceable against, the Pension Fund`
  line `and the beneficiaries under the ceased scheme shall be entitled to draw the benefits, not less than the`
  line `benefits they were entitled to under the ceased scheme, from the Pension Fund.`
  line
  line `(4) The Pension Fund shall vest in and be administered by the Central Board in such manner as may`
  line `be specified in the Pension Scheme.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Pension Scheme may provide for all or any of the matters`
  line `specified in Schedule III.`
  line
  line `(6) The Pension Scheme may provide that all or any of its provisions shall take effect either`
  line `prospectively or retrospectively on such date as may be specified in that behalf in that Scheme.`
  line
  line `(7) A Pension Scheme, framed under sub-section (1), shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made,`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the scheme or both Houses agree that the scheme should not be made, the scheme shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the may be; so, however, that any`
  line `such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that Scheme.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_c:
  sectionId (41425)
  sectionNo 6C
  orderNo 16
  title `Employees' Deposit-linked Insurance Scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41425&sectionno=6C&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_6_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[6C. Employees' Deposit linked Insurance Scheme.-- (1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, frame a scheme to be called the Employees' Deposit-linked Insurance`
  line `Scheme for the purpose of providing life insurance benefits to the employees of any establishment or`
  line `class of establishments to which this Act applies.`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be established, as soon as may be after the framing of the Insurance Scheme, a`
  line `Deposit-linked Insurance Fund into which shall be paid by the employer from time to time in respect of`
  line `every such employee in relation to whom he is the employer, such amount, not being more than one per`
  line `cent. of the aggregate of the basic wages, dearness allowance and retaining allowance (if any) for the time`
  line `being payable in relation to such employee as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the expressions "dearness allowance" and`
  line `"relating allowance" have the same meanings as in section 6.`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(4) (a) The employer shall pay into the Insurance Fund such further sums of money, not exceeding`
  line `one-fourth of the contribution which he is required to make under sub-section (2), as the Central`
  line `Government may, from time to time, determine to meet all the expenses in connection with the`
  line `administration of the Insurance Scheme other than the expenses towards the cost of any benefits provided`
  line `by or under that scheme.`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(5) The Insurance Fund shall vest in the Central Board and be administered by it in such manner as`
  line `may be specified in the Insurance Scheme.`
  line
  line `(6) The Insurance Scheme may provide for all or any of the matters specified in Schedule IV.`
  line
  line `(7) The Insurance Scheme may provide that any of its provisions shall take effect either prospectively`
  line `or retrospectively on such date as may be specified in this behalf in that Scheme.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 99 of 1976, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Omitted by Act 25 of 1996, s. 6 (w.e.f. 16-11-1995)`
obj_root_law_sections_6_d:
  sectionId (41426)
  sectionNo 6D
  orderNo 17
  title `Laying of schemes before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41426&sectionno=6D&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_6_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[6D. Laying of schemes before Parliament.-- Every scheme framed under section 5, section 6A`
  line `and section 6C shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is framed, before each House of Parliament, while`
  line `it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the scheme, or both`
  line `Houses agree that the scheme should not be framed, the scheme shall thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that scheme.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (41427)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 18
  title `Modification of Scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41427&sectionno=7&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, add to,`
  line `^1[amend or vary, either prospectively or retrospectively, the Scheme, the ^2[Family Pension]`
  line `Scheme or the Insurance Scheme, as the case may be].`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Every notification issued under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is issued,`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days, which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the notification, or both Houses agree that the notification should not be issued, the`
  line `notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be;`
  line `so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 99 of 1976, s. 22, for "amend or vary the Scheme or the Family Pension Scheme, as the case may be"`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-8-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 25 of 1996, s. 4, for "Family Pension" (w.e.f. 16-11-1995).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and Schedule, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_a:
  sectionId (41428)
  sectionNo 7A
  orderNo 19
  title `Determination of moneys due from employers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41428&sectionno=7A&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[7A. Determination of moneys due from employers.-- ^2[(1) The Central Provident Fund`
  line `Commissioner, any Additional Central Provident Fund Commissioner, any Deputy Provident Fund`
  line `Commissioner, any Regional Provident Fund Commissioner, or any Assistant Provident Fund`
  line `Commissioner may, by order,--`
  line
  line `(a) in a case where a dispute arises regarding the applicability of this Act to an establishment,`
  line `decide such dispute; and`
  line
  line `(b) determine the amount due from any employer under any provision of this Act, the Scheme or`
  line `the ^3[Pension] Scheme or the Insurance Scheme, as the case may be,`
  line
  line `and for any of the aforesaid purposes may conduct such inquiry as he may deem necessary];`
  line
  line `(2) The officer conducting the inquiry under sub-section (1) shall, for the purposes of such inquiry,`
  line `have the same powers as are vested in a court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), for`
  line `trying a suit in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) enforcing the attendance of any person or examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavit;`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses;`
  line
  line `and any such inquiry shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the meaning of sections 193 and`
  line `228, and for the purpose of section 196, of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(3) No order ^4*** shall be made under sub-section (1), unless ^5[the employer concerned] is given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of representing his case.`
  line
  line `^6[(3A) Where the employer, employee or any other person required to attend the inquiry under`
  line `sub-section (1) fails to attend such inquiry without assigning any valid reason or fails to produce any`
  line `document or to file any report or return when called upon to do so, the officer conducting the inquiry may`
  line `decide the applicability of the Act or determine the amount due from any employer, as the case may be,`
  line `on the basis of the evidence adduced during such inquiry and other documents available on record.]`
  line
  line `^7[(4) Where an order under sub-section (1) is passed against an employer ex parte, he may, within`
  line `three months from the date of communication of such order, apply to the officer for setting aside such`
  line `order and if he satisfies the officer that the show cause notice was not duly served or that he was`
  line `prevented by any sufficient cause from appearing when the inquiry was held, the officer shall make an`
  line `order setting aside his earlier order and shall appoint a date for proceeding with the inquiry:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be set aside merely on the ground that there has been an irregularity`
  line `in the service of the show cause notice if the officer is satisfied that the employer had notice of the date of`
  line `hearing and had sufficient time to appear before the officer.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- Where an appeal has been preferred under this Act against an order passed ex parte`
  line `and such appeal has been disposed of otherwise than on the ground that the appellant has withdrawn the`
  line `appeal, no application shall lie under this sub-section for setting aside the ex parte order.`
  line
  line `(5) No order passed under this section shall be set aside on any application under sub-section (4)`
  line `unless notice thereof has been served on the opposite party].]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 1963, s. 6 (w.e.f. 30-11-1963).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 1988, s. 10, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 1996, s. 4, for "Family Pension" (w.e.f. 16-11-1995).`
  line
  line `4. The words "determining the amount due from employer" omitted by Act 33 of 1988, s. 10. (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for "the employer" (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 1-8-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_b:
  sectionId (41429)
  sectionNo 7B
  orderNo 20
  title `Review of orders passed under section 7A.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 1988, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-7-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41429&sectionno=7B&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_7_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[7B. Review of orders passed under section 7A. -- (1) Any person aggrieved by an order made`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 7A, but from which no appeal has been preferred under this Act, and`
  line `who, from the discovery of new and important matter or evidence which, after the exercise of due`
  line `diligence was not within his knowledge or could not be produced by him at the time when the order was`
  line `made, or on account of some mistake or error apparent on the face of the record or for any other sufficient`
  line `reason, desires to obtain a review of such order may apply for a review of that order to the officer who`
  line `passed the order:`
  line
  line `Provided that such officer may also on his own motion review his order if he is satisfied that it is`
  line `necessary so to do on any such ground.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application for review under sub-section (1) shall be filed in such form and manner and`
  line `within such time as may be specified in the Scheme.`
  line
  line `(3) Where it appears to the officer receiving an application for review that there is no sufficient`
  line `ground for a review, he shall reject the application.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the officer is of opinion that the application for review should be granted, he shall grant the`
  line `same:`
  line
  line `Provided that,--`
  line
  line `(a) no such application shall be granted without previous notice to all the parties before him to`
  line `enable them to appear and be heard in support of the order in respect of which a review is applied`
  line `for, and`
  line
  line `(b) no such application shall be granted on the ground of discovery of new matter or evidence`
  line `which the applicant alleges was not within his knowledge or could not be produced by him when the`
  line `order was made, without proof of such allegation.`
  line
  line `(5) No appeal shall lie against the order of the officer rejecting an application for review, but an`
  line `appeal under this Act shall lie against an order passed under review as if the order passed under review`
  line `were the original order passed by him under section 7A.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_c:
  sectionId (41430)
  sectionNo 7C
  orderNo 21
  title `Determination of escaped amount.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 1988, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-7-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41430&sectionno=7C&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_7_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[7C. Determination of escaped amount.-- Where an order determining the amount due from an`
  line `employer under section 7A or section 7B has been passed and if the officer who passed the order--`
  line
  line `(a) has reason to believe that by reason of the omission or failure on the part of the employer to`
  line `make any document or report available, or to disclose, fully and truly, all material facts necessary for`
  line `determining the correct amount due from the employer, any amount so due from such employer for`
  line `any period has escaped his notice;`
  line
  line `(b) has, in consequence of information in his possession, reason to believe that any amount to be`
  line `determined under section 7A or section 7B has escaped from his determination for any period`
  line `notwithstanding that there has been no omission or failure as mentioned in clause (a) on the part of`
  line `the employer,`
  line
  line `he may, within a period of five years from the date of communication of the order passed under section`
  line `7A or section 7B, re-open the case and pass appropriate orders re-determining the amount due from the`
  line `employer in accordance with the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order re-determining the amount due from the employer shall be passed under this`
  line `section unless the employer is given a reasonable opportunity of representing his case.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_d:
  sectionId (41431)
  sectionNo 7D
  orderNo 22
  title Tribunal
  content `^1[7D Tribunal--The Industrial Tribunal constituted by the Central Government under sub-section (1) of section 7A of the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 shall, on and from the commencement of Part XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017, be the Tribunal for the purposes of this Act and the said Tribunal shall exercise the jurisdiction, powers and authority conferred on it by or under this Act.]`
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 159, for section 7D (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41431&sectionno=7D&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
