obj_root_law_sections_7_i:
  sectionId (41853)
  sectionNo 7-I
  orderNo 27
  title `Appeals to Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_i_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 159, for section 7D (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41853&sectionno=7-I&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_7_i_content:
  string
  line `^1[7-I. Appeals to Tribunal.--(1) Any person aggrieved by a notification issued by the Central Government, or an order passed by the Central Government or any authority, under the proviso to sub-section (3), or sub-section (4), of section 1, or section 3, or sub-section (1) of section 7A, or section 7B`
  line
  line `[except an order rejecting an application for review referred to in sub-section (5) thereof], or section 7C, or section 14B, may prefer an appeal to a Tribunal against such notification or order.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed in such form and manner, within such time and be accompanied by such fees, as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_j:
  sectionId (41436)
  sectionNo 7J
  orderNo 28
  title `Procedure of Tribunals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_j_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 159, for section 7D (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41436&sectionno=7J&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_7_j_content:
  string
  line `^1[7J. Procedure of Tribunals.--(1) A Tribunal shall have power to regulate its own procedure in all matters arising out of the exercise of its powers or of the discharge of its functions including the places at which the Tribunal shall have its sittings.`
  line
  line `(2) A Tribunal shall, for the purpose of discharging its functions, have all the powers which are vested in the officers referred to in section 7A and any proceeding before the Tribunal shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purpose of section 196, of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the Tribunal shall be deemed to be a civil court for the all purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_k:
  sectionId (41854)
  sectionNo 7K
  orderNo 29
  title `Right of appellant to take assistance of legal practitioner and of Government, etc., to appoint presenting officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_k_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 159, for section 7D (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41854&sectionno=7K&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_7_k_content:
  string
  line `^1[7K. Right of appellant to take assistance of legal practitioner and of Government, etc., to appoint presenting officers.---(1) A person preferring an appeal to a Tribunal under this Act may either appear in person or take the assistance of a legal practitioner of his choice to present his case before the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government or a State Government or any other authority under this Act may authorise one or more legal practitioners or any of its officers to act as presenting officers and every person so authorised may present the case with respect to any appeal before a Tribunal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_l:
  sectionId (41438)
  sectionNo 7L
  orderNo 30
  title `Orders of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_l_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 159, for section 7D (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217&sectionId=41438&sectionno=7L&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_6_00038_195219_1517807328217
obj_root_law_sections_7_l_content:
  string
  line `^1[7L. Orders of Tribunal.--(1) A Tribunal may after giving the parties to the appeal, an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit, confirming, modifying or annulling the order appealed against or may refer the case back to the authority which passed such order with such directions as the Tribunal may think fit, for a fresh adjudication or order, as the case may be, after taking additional evidence, if necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) A Tribunal may, at any time within five years from the date of its order, with a view to rectifying any mistake apparent from the record, amend any order passed by it under sub-section (1) and shall make such amendment in the order if the mistake is brought to its notice by the parties to the appeal:`
  line
  line `Provided that an amendment which has the effect of enhancing the amount due from, or otherwise increasing the liability of, the employer shall not be made under this sub-section, unless the Tribunal has given notice to him of its intention to do so and has allowed him a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(3) A Tribunal shall send a copy of every order passed under this section to the parties to the appeal.`
  line
  line `(4) Any order made by a Tribunal finally disposing of an appeal shall not be questioned in any court of law.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_m:
  sectionId (41439)
  sectionNo 7M
  orderNo 31
  title [Omitted.].
  content `[Filling up of vacancies.] Omitted by the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017), s. 159 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
